{"content":"---\ntitle: \"<discoveryClient>\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.assetid: a78f74c3-1152-4149-ab29-3f12d316caeb\n---\n# \\<discoveryClient>\nA configuration element for creating a custom binding that enables a client application to automatically search for a discoverable service and find its address at runtime.  \n  \n\\<system.serviceModel>  \n\\<bindings>  \n\\<customBinding>  \n\\<binding>  \n\\<discoveryClient>  \n  \n## Syntax  \n  \n```xml  \n<discoveryClient discoveryEndpoint=\"String\">\n  <findCriteria duration=\"TimeSpan\"\n                maxResults=\"Integer\"\n                scopeMatchBy=\"Uri\">\n    <contractTypeNames>\n      <add name=\"String\"\n           namespace=\"String\" />\n    </contractTypeNames>\n    <extensions />\n    <scopes>\n      <add scope=\"URI\"/>\n    </scopes>\n  </findCriteria>\n</discoveryClient>\n```  \n  \n## Attributes and Elements  \n The following sections describe attributes, child elements, and parent elements.  \n  \n### Attributes  \n  \n|Attribute|Description|  \n|---------------|-----------------|  \n|discoveryEndpoint|A string that contains the name of the Discovery Endpoint that enables a client application to automatically search for a discoverable service and find its address at runtime.|  \n  \n### Child Elements  \n  \n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<standardEndpoints>](../../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/wcf/standardendpoints.md)|A configuration element that supplies a set of criteria used by a client application to search for a discovery service. Criteria can be grouped into search criteria (specifying what services you’re looking for) and find termination criteria (how long the search should last).|  \n  \n### Parent Elements  \n  \n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<binding>](../../../../../docs/framework/misc/binding.md)|Defines all binding capabilities of the custom binding.|  \n  \n## See also\n\n- <xref:System.ServiceModel.Discovery.DiscoveryClientBindingElement>\n- <xref:System.ServiceModel.Discovery.Configuration.DiscoveryClientElement>\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,101],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"<discoveryClient>\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.assetid: a78f74c3-1152-4149-ab29-3f12d316caeb","nodes":[{"content":"<discoveryClient>","nodes":[],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[108,126],"content":"\\<discoveryClient>","linkify":"\\<discoveryClient>","nodes":[{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>discoveryClient&gt;","pos":[0,18],"source":"\\<discoveryClient>"}]},{"content":"A configuration element for creating a custom binding that enables a client application to automatically search for a discoverable service and find its address at runtime.","pos":[127,298]},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>system.serviceModel&gt;","pos":[304,326],"source":"\\<system.serviceModel>"},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>bindings&gt;","pos":[329,340],"source":"\\<bindings>"},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>customBinding&gt;","pos":[343,359],"source":"\\<customBinding>"},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>binding&gt;","pos":[362,372],"source":"\\<binding>"},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>discoveryClient&gt;","pos":[375,393],"source":"\\<discoveryClient>"},{"pos":[402,408],"content":"Syntax","linkify":"Syntax","nodes":[{"content":"Syntax","pos":[0,6]}]},{"pos":[804,827],"content":"Attributes and Elements","linkify":"Attributes and Elements","nodes":[{"content":"Attributes and Elements","pos":[0,23]}]},{"content":"The following sections describe attributes, child elements, and parent elements.","pos":[831,911]},{"pos":[921,931],"content":"Attributes","linkify":"Attributes","nodes":[{"content":"Attributes","pos":[0,10]}]},{"content":"Attribute","pos":[938,947]},{"content":"Description","pos":[948,959]},{"content":"discoveryEndpoint","pos":[1002,1019]},{"content":"A string that contains the name of the Discovery Endpoint that en